headline: Super Micro (SMCI) Stock Trades Down, Here Is Why
summary: Shares of server solutions provider Super Micro (NASDAQ:SMCI) fell 5.7% in the afternoon session after significant bearish options activity was detected, continuing a period of weakness for the stock. An analysis of unusual trades revealed that 60% of traders showed bearish tendencies. headline: Nvidia, bitcoin and other falling stars drag the US stock market lower
summary: The U.S. stock market sank Monday as Nvidia and other superstars created by the frenzy around artificial-intelligence  technology dimmed some more.  Nvidia was the heaviest weight on the market, as it’s often been in its last couple of tumultuous weeks. The chip company fell 1.8%, while losses for other AI winners included a 6.4% slide for Super Micro Computer.
